            "author_info": {
                "name": "David Vandevoorde",
                "href": "/profile/David-Vandevoorde"
            },
            "answer_text": "Kotlin can stand on its own: No need to learn Java first. Kotlin is a newer language that takes advantage of some technology that was first developed for Java, but that technology is also used for other languages (like Scala and a version of Python) and those languages don\u2019t require learning Java first either. That said, the common underlying technology means that you can easily use Java libraries from Kotlin. The documentation for those libraries may assume Java client code (because Java is still much more popular than Kotlin at this time), and in that sense understanding Java could be useful in your use of Kotlin. However, that\u2019s unlikely to be an issue during the initial learning stages with Kotlin. ",
