                "href": "/profile/Malcolm-Teas"
            },
            "answer_text": "In the Android world there are many thousands of apps written in Java. In most companies, that isn\u2019t going to get converted over to Kotlin anytime soon. It\u2019s working code after all. And if it gets re-written in Kotlin, new bugs will be accidentally introduced. This will be true for years. So if you want to have full career in Android development, you need to know both. There\u2019s more things out there showing Java examples and teaching than Kotlin, so from that view it makes sense to learn Java first. But technically either language can be learned first. ",
